<b>Adrian Bowyer</b> is a British engineer and mathematician, currently a lecturer at the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../992/153992.xml">
University of Bath</link>.<p>

Born in 1952 in London, Bowyer is the older child of the late Rosemary and John Bowyer; the latter was a writer, painter and one of the founders of <weblink xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://www.zbp.co.uk/start.htm">
Zisman, Bowyer and Partners</weblink>, consulting engineers. </p>
<p>

Adrian Bowyer was educated at <weblink xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://www.woodroffe.dorset.sch.uk/">
Woodroffe School</weblink>, <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../892/194892.xml">
Lyme Regis</link></site>
 and <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../116/61116.xml">
Imperial College London</link></university>
.</p>
<p>

In 1977 he joined the Mathematics Department at the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../992/153992.xml">
University of Bath</link>. Shortly after that he received a doctorate from Imperial for research in friction-induced vibration.</p>
<p>

